subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is known from all Islands of French West Indies ( Kreiter and Moraes 1997 ;
Moraes et al. 2000
;
Kreiter et al. 2006
, 2018c ;
Mailloux et al. 2010
), but it was found only in very large numbers during a previous study on companion plants in Guadeloupe (
Mailloux et
al. 2010) and in a study on La Réunion (Le Bellec, unpub. data). This species seems to be very abundant on weeds in the lower vegetation. Phytoseiid mites of the genus
Proprioseiopsis
had been found mainly in ground surface, humus, litter, soil, moss or on grass (
Muma and Denmark
1970;
McMurtry et al. 2015
).
